Class MultipleStringSetEditor

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.awt.Component
      • java.awt.Container
        • java.awt.Window
          • java.awt.Dialog
            • javax.swing.JDialog
              • com.cafean.client.ui.beans.MultipleStringSetEditor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IntrospectingEditor, java.awt.image.ImageObserver, java.awt.MenuContainer, java.beans.PropertyEditor, java.io.Serializable, javax.accessibility.Accessible, javax.swing.RootPaneContainer, javax.swing.WindowConstants
    public class MultipleStringSetEditor
extends javax.swing.JDialog
implements IntrospectingEditor
    Edits a String[] in the currently edited object called selected that has a String[] called choices that can be selected to be part of the array.

    Also allows for an optional String[] called descriptions that is parallel to choices and is added to the editor to describe each choice.

    Note that both choices and descriptions are static arrays.
